Package hms.appointments

Class DoctorSchedule

java.lang.Object
hms.appointments.DoctorSchedule
public class DoctorSchedule extends Object
The DoctorSchedule class is responsible for managing a doctor's schedule for a given date, including working hours and breaks. It allows a doctor to input their availability, which can be queried later to check if they are available at specific times.

  • Method Details

    • setWorkingTime

      protected void setWorkingTime()
      Sets the working time by prompting the user for the start and end times. The user is asked to input the times in the format of hours and minutes. The input values are then used to create Time objects for startTime and endTime.

    • setBreaks

      protected void setBreaks()
      Prompts the user to input the number of breaks they would like to add, and collects the start and end times for each break. The method ensures that the break start time is before the break end time and calls the mergeBreaks(Time, Time) method to process each valid break.
